comments.text: L210W is a TAM that usually occurs in combination with M41L and T215Y. The combination of M41, L210W and T215Y causes high-level resistance to AZT and d4T and intermediate to high-level resistance to ddI, ABC and TDF.
T215Y is a TAM that causes intermediate/high-level resistance to AZT and d4T, low-level resistance to ddI, and potentially low-level resistance to ABC and TDF.
